{
  "legislative_session": "153",
  "identifier": "HB 335",
  "title": "AN ACT TO AMEND TITLE 29 OF THE DELAWARE CODE RELATING TO THE STATE LOTTERY.",
  "from_organization": "~{\"classification\": \"lower\"}",
  "classification": [
    "bill"
  ],
  "subject": [],
  "abstracts": [
    {
      "note": "synopsis",
      "abstract": "This bill protects small businesses in Delaware by preserving lottery retailers\u2019 role in iLottery. This bill requires iLottery players to purchase prepaid cards at physical stores to enable their online play.  \r\n\r\nIn 2012, the General Assembly adopted the Delaware Gaming Competitiveness Act of 2012, HB 333 of the 146th General Assembly, establishing iLottery in Delaware. To support small businesses, the General Assembly included a provision of that law that required online players to purchase prepaid cards in physical retail stores. However, over a decade later, the Delaware Lottery Commissioner launched an iLottery program that does not uphold this protective provision. This bill updates the iLottery program to reflect the original intent of the law. \r\n\r\nThis Act also makes technical changes to conform to the Legislative Drafting Manual."
    }
  ],
